content:
David Matas, avocat spécialisé en droits de l'homme

M. David Matas s'adresse au public lors de la projection du film.

Après la présentation de M. Matas, certains membres de l'auditoire ont demandé ce qui pouvait être fait pour mettre fin au prélèvement forcé d'organes. M. Matas a répondu que la technologie médicale avait été développée pour améliorer la santé et le niveau de vie des populations, mais qu'en Chine, elle était détournée et utilisée comme un outil pour commettre des violations des droits humains à grande échelle et des massacres. Il a souligné que face à ce problème, le secteur médical et des citoyens de tous horizons ont commencé à agir.

Au Japon, une nouvelle législation a été demandée pour interdire le tourisme de transplantation d'organes, et de nombreuses personnes ont contribué à diffuser des informations sur les atrocités commises en Chine. La projection du film a souligné l'importance de ne pas rester indifférent au problème du prélèvement forcé d'organes et de faire ce qui est en son pouvoir. Il a été souligné qu'il est crucial que davantage de personnes s'intéressent à ce problème et agissent pour promouvoir sa résolution par la diffusion d'informations et des campagnes de collecte de signatures.

Les prélèvements forcés d'organes par le PCC ont été révélés pour la première fois par des témoins ayant fui la Chine, et des enquêtes ont été menées sur la base de leurs témoignages. Plusieurs films ont été réalisés pour dénoncer ces violations flagrantes des droits humains. Malgré le peu de témoins et la difficulté d'obtenir des preuves, de nombreuses personnes ont déployé des efforts considérables pour que ce problème ne tombe pas dans l'oubli.


M. David Matas

Au cours du film et des discussions qui ont suivi, il est apparu clairement que le prélèvement forcé d'organes en Chine est un crime organisé auquel l'État participe et qui cible les prisonniers d'opinion, principalement les pratiquants de Falun Gong. La communauté internationale a exprimé sa vive inquiétude face à la situation en Chine.

Les témoignages des pratiquants de Falun Gong jouent un rôle important dans la dénonciation des prélèvements forcés d'organes. Ils indiquent que des pratiquants de Falun Gong ont subi des analyses sanguines en prison, et que nombre d'entre eux ont tout simplement disparu. Ces tests de compatibilité avec les transplantations d'organes sont en cours, et les données biographiques des pratiquants de Falun Gong sont intégrées à une immense base de données. Les personnes sélectionnées comme donneurs d'organes sont tuées lors de la transplantation.

content:
Stand Up to Support and Spread the Truth
Dr. Cheng Cheng-bing said, “This film screening is very successful. It’s great! I’m very moved!” He gave a thumbs up and said, “We are very grateful to Falun Gong practitioners, The Epoch Times, Sound of Hope, and other media outlets that report on this. You are all dedicated and selfless, which is really amazing.”


Dr. Cheng Cheng-bing

He said, “Each of us should learn this spirit, stand up to support, and have the courage to expose the truth and fight against the CCP.”

More People Should Support This Film
After Rotary Club member Ms. Tsai Han-lin watched the film she said, “I was deeply moved. I admire Falun Gong practitioners very much. In the past, I only heard that they were persecuted, but I didn’t know why and couldn’t understand it. Now I understand it clearly.”


Rotary Club member Ms. Tsai Han-lin

She said that everyone should volunteer to promote this film, and everyone in Taiwan should watch it, “Although we cannot save these persecuted people, we should volunteer, support and rescue them. This is what we should do.

“This movie can really save Taiwan, Falun Gong practitioners, myself, my children, family and friends. I will tell more people about it. Everyone should support this movie.”

Another audience member said, “The discussion was successful and informative. What several professors talked about helps motivate young students and audience members to safeguard democracy, freedom, and human rights. My child told me, ‘Mom, send me the website of the movie State Organs. I will show it to my classmates and friends who didn’t come. I will share it in my groups on Facebook so that more people can watch it. This is very important. We must take the initiative to protect our country and safeguard our democracy, freedom and human rights. Everyone has this responsibility.’”

Yu Guan said, “The screening and discussion went well.” He said that his friend read the false reports in overseas media last week, but after watching the movie he understood the truth and asked how to learn Falun Gong.

content:
Danish Officials Question the Source of the Bodies
Morten Messerschmidt, Danish MP (Member of Parliament) and chairman of the People’s Party (Dansk Folkeparti) was shocked by the exhibition. On February 7, he asked the Minister of Health several questions about the law, ethics and China’s use of political prisoners’ organs:


Morten Messerschmidt, MP and chairman of the People’s Party, asked the Minister of Health questions about ethical issues regarding the body exhibition.

Question 275: “Can you explain what permits and legal procedures are required for the exhibition of human remains in Denmark and whether the exhibition of human remains complies with applicable laws?”

Question 276: “Can the Minister explain how the use of human remains in exhibitions should ensure the consent of the deceased or their relatives? “

Question 277: “Will the Minister comment on the ethical considerations in connection with the commercial use of human bodies in exhibitions such as Human-Bodies, including whether the current rules are sufficient, or whether there should be stricter rules for such exhibitions in Denmark?”

Question No. 278: “Will the Minister investigate whether he is aware of similar exhibitions of human bodies internationally that are related to lack of consent or illegal trade, and whether the Minister will investigate human bodies in this regard? In this context, is the Minister aware of China’s use of organs from political prisoners?”

Søren Espersen, a senior member of the Danish Democratic Party (Danmarksdemokraterne) and chairman of the Religious Committee, asked the Minister of Culture on February 19: “Can it be determined with certainty that all bodies and body parts are donated voluntarily, do not originate from, for example, executed prisoners in dictatorships, or originate from illegal organ trafficking?”


Søren Espersen, a senior member of the Danish Democratic Party, asked the Minister of Culture about the bodies.

“The exhibition has been criticized in several places because of doubts that the bodies were not all donated voluntarily and for a clear purpose,” Thomas Krarup, director of health, culture and care in the city of Randers, wrote in a notification to government authorities.

content:
Le documentaire « Organes d'État » a été projeté à Tokyo le 26 mars 2025. L'avocat canadien des droits de la personne, David Matas, y a donné une conférence dans le cadre d'une campagne de sensibilisation au prélèvement forcé d'organes sur des prisonniers d'opinion par le Parti communiste chinois (PCC). La projection de « Organes d'État » vise à dénoncer les violations des droits de la personne en Chine, à sensibiliser le public à la question des prélèvements forcés d'organes et à promouvoir la coopération au sein de la communauté internationale pour mettre fin à ces atrocités et protéger la vie et la dignité des personnes.

Le film, réalisé pendant environ sept ans, documente les prélèvements forcés d'organes sur des pratiquants de Falun Gong, violemment persécutés par le PCC depuis 1999. Le film, qui inclut des témoignages, s'ouvre sur le témoignage bouleversant de l'ancien chirurgien M. Zheng Zhi, témoin vivant des prélèvements. Il présente également des enregistrements de militants des droits de l'homme étrangers se faisant passer pour des patients et appelant des hôpitaux chinois pour s'enquérir de la rapidité des transplantations et savoir si les organes provenaient de pratiquants de Falun Gong.

Le documentaire dépeint également la douleur des familles de pratiquants de Falun Gong disparus : un père tente par tous les moyens de sauver son fils ; un frère se prépare mentalement à affronter la nouvelle de sa mort. Le public a été profondément touché par ces témoignages.

Le directeur des Organes d'État , Zhang Yongjin, a expliqué que les prélèvements forcés d'organes ne sont qu'une facette de la campagne génocidaire du PCC contre le Falun Gong. Il a ajouté que tant que le régime totalitaire perdurera, les violations des droits de l'homme seront dissimulées et le nombre de victimes continuera d'augmenter.

content:
Heres my analysis (without looking at genius or reddit or anything else). Obviously we don't have the full album yet to see the full context, so all of this is a huge educated guess:

This song describes a long journey at sea, where each verse is a moment in time. The first verse is "that time of the year where i start getting old". This is reffering to quadecas birthday, which takes place in early october

The second verse "that time of the year where theres smoke in my breath", which would be winter (another note, i didnt know that a "down" was a feather until this song)

The third verse is when the "lights getting strong and it's blocking my path", which could be spring or summer (probably summer)

"Monday" in the chorus is metaphorical, as representing the start of something bigger (even though that start can be painful). Quadeca is telling his love interest not to give up on their relationship when its only just started

Hope that this was at least somewhat useful to someone

As the world pauses reflecting about the death of the pope, prophecy invites us to consider the true spiritual significance of this global admiration—not with hostility, but with spiritual discernment and urgency:

This beast power is a symbol, not of a person, but of *a religious-political system [Papacy] that the Bible predicted would rise to global prominence. Through compromise and tradition, it replaces the authority of God's Word with human decrees.

📌 Who Is the Beast?
- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
According to prophetic study:
1. It receives power and a throne from the dragon[Roman Empire ~ Satan] (Revelation 13:2).

❛ Let no one deceive you by any means; for that Day will not come unless the falling away comes first, and the man of sin is revealed… ❜
— 2 Thessalonians 2:3 (NKJV)

❛ Come out of her, My people, lest you share in her sins… ❜
— Revelation 18:4 (NKJV)

This is a call:
1. To Return to the Bible

3. To prepare for the soon return of Christ.

📌 What You Can Do

🌍 The world may marvel—but God’s people must awaken.

content:
Dear Fortnite Team,

I hope this message finds you well. I’m writing as a longtime fan and dedicated player of Fortnite to express a concern that I know is shared by many in the community.

Over the past few seasons, the movement animations in the game have changed significantly. While the newer mechanics like sprinting, mantling, and sliding have added fresh dynamics to the gameplay, many players—including myself—feel that the updated animations have taken away from the original feel and flow of the game. The older movement animations were smoother, more natural, and simply felt better when building or navigating the map.

A large portion of the Fortnite community has voiced their desire to see the original movement animations return. Many players have even stepped away from the game because of how different and, frankly, awkward the new animations feel in comparison. It would mean a lot to many of us if Epic could consider adding the old movement animations back—whether as a setting toggle, in Creative mode, or as part of the OG game mode.

To be clear, we’re not asking to remove the newer mechanics like sprinting or mantling—those are great additions! We’re just hoping the classic animations could make a return to preserve the unique feeling that made Fortnite so enjoyable in its earlier days. Not only would this move show that Epic is listening to its community, but I truly believe it could help bring back a lot of players and boost engagement overall.

Thank you for taking the time to consider this feedback. We all love Fortnite, and we want to see it continue to thrive.

content:
Guys, don't skimp on cheese and get the authentic stuff. You'll find it's a fascinating world that you can become a real nerd over. Me and my 7 year old daughter take turns choosing a new cheese every 2-4 weeks to try and we really do bond over our little cheese hobby. That 7 year old has had cheeses that would make a grown adults toes curl and stomach churn. Shes had authentic Roquefort and adores it. Thats so putrid, that the mold has a crystalline texture.

Italian hard cheeses are what I consider the "witchcraft" cheeses. Because if I bite any Italian hard cheese, I take an instant dislike. But when you introduce a cheese grater and grate the cheese, it has this magical formation and becomes something really, really special. We made an authentic carbonara the other week so had to get Pecorino Romano, one bite and I thought "perfect, smells and tastes like hooves walked through sheep wee." We continued with our first authentic carbonara and it was unbelievable, I don't even like Italian food and came to the conclusion that I've just not ever had authentic Italian food because this hit so different.

I can't wait to explore more Italian cheese.

content:
Man, when Reflect dropped I listened to that song over and over, so many times. It gave me goosebumps and was just such a well composed song, one of the very few videos I've actually liked, coincidentally my most recent like before this one. Now all these years later, Ash Again has taken the same spot in my mind, going to be listening to this periodically for probably months, albeit with a much more somber energy. The emotions in this song are just so potent, I definitely didn't tear up a bit when the other members of myth, Ame in particular, showed up.

This silly little shark is the person who really got me into VTubing in the first place, and while I've since stopped watching VTubers in general all that much, she was always one I'd come back to. Sad to see you go, Gura, but I wish you the best wherever you go from here, and thank you for all the laughs along the way.

content:
How to win final game as impostor:

1. As Escapist - set your marker at left-most side in reactor.
2. Since Josh was following Lazar and he can’t be killed without Lazar getting voted, get him to follow you to the teleport which he will likely do since there’s nothing else to do.
3. Teleport into one of the nodes.
4. Run from that node to the other while Josh is following.
5. While Josh is following, close him in the airlock.
6. Josh gets sucked into the airlock, meaning they can’t report the body since there is no body.
7. Wait for your sabotage cooldown to reset.
8. Reactor is the only sabotage where the other two players are guaranteed to be in the same place simultaneously, both Vik and Ethan will be there unless they want to lose.
9. While reactor is called, emergency meetings are disabled, making it impossible for them to vote you out (No meetings allowed, and no body to report.)
9. Use your marker from the start of the round to teleport back to the reactor.
10. Since Josh was killed in the airlock, there will be no kill cooldown (you yourself never killed in the round)
11. Wait for them to come to the reactor.
12. Kill them when they try to fix it and win the game.
13. If they don’t fix it, the game will end as impostor victory regardless.

content:
THE DATAMINED PICS DO NOT PROVE ''REMASTER''!
It's entirely possible that the "remaster" images discovered on Virtuos' site were placeholders or early concepts that remained untouched behind the scenes on their site, while the project evolved behind the scenes. Game development often involves layers of complexity, and assets might linger until they're replaced by updated ones more aligned with the final vision. If Bethesda and Virtuos pivoted to a remake, they might have intentionally held back those newer pics to make a splash with the official reveal. So what was found on their site, could have been an old and outdated plan!!! Simply not updated yet.

content:
Everyone’s clapping for this song like it’s some deep reflection on mental health, but let’s be real—it barely scratches the surface. “Anxiety” isn’t just feeling off or misunderstood, it’s panic attacks, restlessness, sleepless nights, and a constant battle with your own brain. What Doechii did here is more aesthetic than authentic. It’s anxiety as a vibe, not a lived experience.

We owe an apology to KSI 🥀

content:
My thoughts on the episode: the characters were great, so dynamic and energetic. I loved Mud especially, so funny and conniving. Mel is my second fav, she is such a great protagonist for many reasons, and I love how cunning and eccentric she is along some other things which I can't talk about right now cuz wifi bad.
Ken Is a great father figure despite being overprotective. He definitely knows a lot more than he let's on and I'm curious to learn it. Also notice his brain kinda switches to the other side sometimes? He is bipolar and u can't change my mind.
I liked breadhead as well but not enough screen time for me to like him remotely as much as the other 3. still a pretty neat character with plenty of potential.
Also wanna praise the animation, something which I don't think can be done enough. It has so much detail and is near perfect.

content: Sometimes humour covers an uncomfortable truth. I spent some time in Australia … really did not feel comfortable… Australia’s reputation ( which is true) as well functioning, clean and extremely law abiding, also comes with the reputation that if you so much as break one little law you will be hunted down, shackled and deported… so for example in Australia I didn’t rent a car .. to scared that I might accidentally break a speed limit I don’t know about or park in a parking bay I didn’t know I couldn’t park in. I felt that I was constantly being watched by Australian’s for even the slightest error. Interesting because I have no problem walking around “Boca” in Buenos Aires or Cairo or Johannesburg or any other “dangerous” or “ dangerous “ part of a city .. simply because you feel that if you accidentally did something you would be understood by the locals and local authorities. In Australia ( Sydney and Brisbane) I felt like I was in North Korea … that all anyone wanted to do was find a reason … to punish you for something ..  like I said it’s probably just me but Australia creating series like “Border Control” … made it seem like they view tourists as a menace and treat you like a criminal just for arriving. I was honestly surprised that  I was just waived through visa and border control when I arrived !!

content:
The documentary State Organs was screened in Taiwan in October 2024, and the audience responded enthusiastically. Despite threatening letters from the Chinese Communist Party (CCP) the film was shown nearly 300 times across Taiwan, giving people the opportunity to understand the nature of the CCP. On January 11, 2025, the documentary was screened again at the Yunlin County Labor Recreation Center in Taiwan, and a discussion was held afterwards.

The discussion was hosted by Dr. Yu Hui-yun, Associate Professor of the Department of Business Administration at Yunlin University of Science and Technology. Mr. Li Cheng-hsiung, a master of law from the University of Notre Dame and former prosecutor of the Military District Prosecutor’s Office, and Dr. Cheng Cheng-bing, professor of the Department of Finance at Yunlin University of Science and Technology and editor-in-chief of the magazine, Thinking and Speaking, answered audience members’ questions.

Mr. Li said there were many threatening messages since the film began being shown in Taiwan: including threats of bombs being planted and petrol bombs being thrown, as well as breaking in venues to stab or shoot people. These threats were made in an attempt to stop the organizers from showing the film. The organizers overcame their fear, insisted on exposing the truth, and continued showing the film.


Mr. Li Cheng-hsiung, former prosecutor of the Military District Prosecutor’s Office, talks with audience members.

He said that when Chinese military doctor Zheng Zhi came to Taiwan, he revealed that the military hospital asked him to come up with a plan: “How to take the organs of Taiwanese people and transplant them into wounded Chinese soldiers during wartime, occupy the island and eliminate the residents.” When talking about the CCP’s forced organ harvesting from Falun Gong practitioners, Zheng Zhi said, “You Taiwanese are so kind. They (the CCP) treat people as human mines, and treat Taiwanese people the same as Falun Gong practitioners. There are only 23 million people in Taiwan, so occupying the island and eliminating the residents would be a trivial thing for the CCP.”

Zheng Zhi also described the CCP’s brutal and inhumane treatment of its own soldiers. He said that when a senior CCP official had an eye disease, the doctors at a military hospital discussed how to harvest the eyes from a pilot who had excellent eyesight. The selected pilot’s eyes were removed while he was alive. He was the 18-year-old soldier in the movie. His throat was cut so he could not scream, and he was not given anesthesia. Zheng Zhi said the CCP treats its own soldiers so cruelly.

“The military has long been engaged in live organ harvesting, and does it secretly to serve their superiors,” he said. “They have no scruples in framing and accusing Falun Gong practitioners, imprisoning them on trumped-up charges, and wantonly suppressing them by harvesting their organs while they are alive.”

author: @bryanthernandez9769

content:
Comment:

Alright, I gotta be honest… Star Wars: Zero Company? That name needs to go. It doesn’t hit at all. Sounds more like a beta test title or a placeholder from early development. If you want fans to actually remember this game and be hyped for it—especially Clone Wars fans—you need something bolder. Something that screams Star Wars, Republic, tactics, whatever. Just not Zero Company.

Also, why is this not coming to mobile? It’s a strategy game. That’s the kind of stuff that belongs on mobile. Strategy games are made for quick sessions—whether you’re sitting on the toilet, waiting at the doctor’s office, or killing time with one AirPod in at a boring event. That’s where games like this shine. You barely see strategy games truly thrive on console or PC unless they’re niche or emulated, and even then they don’t fully take off. Star Wars fans need a mobile Clone Wars strategy game. It just makes sense.

Please consider changing the name and getting this thing on mobile. You’ll reach way more fans, especially those of us who grew up with the Clone Wars and still game on the go. Don’t miss the opportunity.

content:
2 years ago on April 19th, 2023, the world lost a bright star, a soul whose light shone so brightly but was hidden behind a pain we could never truly understand. Moonbin’s passing left a void, a quiet, aching silence in the hearts of many, and yet, in the midst of that silence, his presence is still felt.
As the days go by, we are reminded of the beauty he brought into our lives, the joy he spread through his music, his art, and his kind heart. But today, we also feel the weight of the words left unsaid, the moments lost to darkness. He was more than a performer, more than a star—he was a person with dreams, hopes, and an immense capacity to love. And though he is no longer here with us, his legacy lives on in every smile, every note, every memory he shared.
Moonbin, you will never be forgotten. You were loved more than words can express, and your memory will live in our hearts forever. We hold onto the love you gave us, and we carry it forward with us, trying to be as kind, as loving, and as strong as you were. Rest in peace, angel. You are missed beyond measure.😭💗💫✨

content:
The Australian Senate passed a new bill on August 21, 2024, that aims to fight illegal organ trafficking and forced organ harvesting from living people.


Parliament House in Canberra, Australia

The Migration Amendment (Overseas Organ Transplant Disclosure and Other Measures) Bill 2023 was first introduced by Liberal Senator Dean Smith in June 2023. It was submitted to Foreign Affairs, Defense and Trade Legislation Committee for review in November. The Senate held a public hearing on the Amendment on March 22, 2024.

After the debates on August 15 and 21, the bill was passed after gaining support from Liberal, National, Green, and independent senators.

In the process of the bill being passed, the story of Falun Gong practitioner Mr. Cheng Peiming was widely reported by major media outlets in England, the U.S., and Australia. Mr. Cheng is the first victim found to have survived the Chinese Communist Party’s (CCP) systematic live organ harvesting. Last month he went to Washington D.C. to give a speech and recount his experience of what happened to him in China.

Senator Smith: Most Significant Step
The bill amends Australia’s Migration Act 1958 with an aim to implement some of the recommendations from the Human Rights Sub-Committee’s 2018 report “Compassion, not Commerce: An Inquiry into Human Organ Trafficking and Organ Transplant Tourism.”

The bill requires all travelers to Australia to disclose on the incoming passenger card whether they received an organ transplant overseas in the last five years. If the response is affirmative, persons arriving in Australia will be asked to disclose which country, state, and the locality they received the transplant, and the name of the medical facility the operation took place in. This data will be collected and published in an annual report and given to the Parliament.


Liberal Senator for Western Australia Dean Smith spoke at the debate on the Amendment on August 21. (Photo courtesy Australia Senate website)

Bill sponsor Senator Dean Smith stated in a media release on August 21, 2024: “The information will be of great assistance to human rights organisations, medical institutions, and the Australian Government in analysing data on trends in overseas transplants, and helping to corroborate existing evidence of organ trafficking or harvesting activities abroad.

“It will also serve to raise awareness of the sensitivity and risks associated with transplant tourism, encouraging Australian citizens and residents to consider whether any plans to receive an overseas operation might carry the risks associated with an unethical or unsafe organ transplant.”

According to the media release, “The bill passed the Senate with the support of crossbench Senators and without a division.”

Senator Smith said, “This is the most significant step made in decades in emboldening Australia’s efforts to combat the growing trade in illegal and unethical organ harvesting and trafficking.

“This is an overdue and crucial first step in developing a stronger response from the Australian Government towards these abhorrent practices.” “This simple and modest initiative will have an oversized impact in uncovering the scope of this complex and opaque international crime.”

The bill will now move to the House of Representatives for further debate.

content:
All glory be to God and praise Him for the resurrection which is our destination whether in the grave or caught up alive to meet them in the clouds and be with the Lord for ever. Amen, and Amen!
+
Give your life to the Lord. Amen!
+
Trust in Jesus Christ, not antichrist.
+
I hope and pray that folks change their view and invite the Lord Jesus Christ into their life to rule and reign.
+
Satan is referred to as the prince of the power of the air for good reason, he owns the airwaves on planet earth and is the god (little g) of this world. It is my hope and prayer that you choose the God (Big G) of heaven who controls the destiny of your eternal soul.
+
(Matthew 10:28 > And fear not them which kill the body, but are not able to kill the soul: but rather fear him which is able to destroy both soul and body in hell.
+
(2 Corinthians 4:3-4 > [3]-But if our gospel be hid, it is hid to them that are lost:
[4]-In whom the god of this world hath blinded the minds of them which believe not, lest the light of the glorious gospel of Christ, who is the image of God, should shine unto them.)

(Romans 10:9-10 > [9]-That if thou shalt confess with thy mouth the Lord Jesus, and shalt believe in thine heart that God hath raised him from the dead, thou shalt be saved.
[10]-For with the heart man believeth unto righteousness; and with the mouth confession is made unto salvation.)

(Romans 10:13 > For whosoever shall call upon the name of the Lord shall be saved.)

(Ephesians 2:8-9 > [8]-For by grace are ye saved through faith; and that not of yourselves: it is the gift of God:
[9]-Not of works, lest any man should boast.)

(Revelation 3:20 > Behold, I stand at the door, and knock: if any man hear my voice, and open the door, I will come in to him, and sup with him, and he with me.)

Is Jesus knocking at the door of your heart?
Is this your opportunity for eternal salvation?
If it is, I hope and pray that you open the door and invite Him, (Jesus), into your heart and life, in Jesus' name. Amen!

All praise and glory be to God. Amen!

content:
A German company held a human body exhibition in several cities in Denmark from early November 2024 to early March 2025. Because the exhibition organizers could not prove where the specimens came from, and because there is evidence of systematic persecution of Falun Gong practitioners and dissidents as well as forced organ harvesting in China, many people in Denmark had questions.

Danish parliamentarians, government officials in the cities where the exhibition was held, mainstream media, the venue renters, and ordinary people all expressed concern about the source of the corpses. Many people expressed their support for Falun Gong practitioners’ efforts to expose the Chinese Communist Party’s (CCP) persecution.

According to the investigation by the World Organization to Investigate the Persecution of Falun Gong (WOIPFG) on the source of corpses in China’s plastination human specimen industry: In 2008, at the request of the New York State Attorney General, Sui Hongjin [Note: Chairman of Dalian Hongfeng, a company that uses Chinese corpses to make plastinated human specimens] partner Premier Exhibitions posted a “disclaimer” on the exhibition’s official website and the New York exhibition site, which made public the original source of the human specimens from Dalian Hongfeng: “The remains of Chinese citizens or residents exhibited in this exhibition come from the Chinese police.”

The first paragraph of the disclaimer of the First Exhibition Company in the United States states: The remains of Chinese citizens or residents on display in this exhibition come from the Chinese police, who may have obtained these bodies from Chinese prisons. Premier Exhibition cannot independently confirm that the bodies you see are not those detained in Chinese prisons.

content:
I wasted way too much of my life playing video games, especially the Elder Scrolls series. And I would advise people to do the same as me and hang up the controllers, and by a King James Bible.
It has the most epic stories in it, from the creation of heaven, earth, and God's prize creation the human race, starting with Adam, then Eve being created from the rib of Adam.
+
The reason Adam was God's crowning creation is because he was created in the image of God, with a body, soul, and spirit, where the angels only have body and spirit.
+
The storyline is incredible, with more than 40 holy men, over 4,000 years, chosen by God, to pen what God inspires them to write / record. And yet all books of the KJV bible never contradict each other at any time.
+
It gives you the history of God's chosen people, their epic battles, their ups and downs, and their defiance of the God that not only created them, but tolerated their sin against Him and their following of the enemy of God, one of His angels who chose to rebel, "a fallen angel", better know as lucifer or Satan.
+

content:
Fleiri ættu að styðja þessa mynd
Eftir að meðlimur Rótarýklúbbsins fröken Tsai Han-lin horfði á myndina sagði hún: "Ég var djúpt snortin. Ég dáist mjög að Falun Gong iðkendum. Áður fyrr heyrði ég aðeins að þeir væru ofsóttir, en ég vissi ekki hvers vegna og gat ekki skilið það. Nú skil ég það greinilega."


Rótarýklúbbsmeðlimur fröken Tsai Han-lin

Hún sagði að allir ættu að bjóða sig fram til að kynna þessa mynd og allir í Taívan ættu að horfa á hana, „Þó að við getum ekki bjargað þessu ofsótta fólki, ættum við að bjóða sig fram, styðja og bjarga því. Þetta er það sem við ættum að gera.

"Þessi mynd getur virkilega bjargað Taívan, Falun Gong iðkendum, mér, börnum mínum, fjölskyldu og vinum. Ég mun segja fleirum frá henni. Allir ættu að styðja þessa mynd."

Annar áheyrandi sagði: "Umræðan var árangursrík og fræðandi. Það sem nokkrir prófessorar ræddu um hjálpar til við að hvetja unga nemendur og áhorfendur til að standa vörð um lýðræði, frelsi og mannréttindi. Barnið mitt sagði við mig: "Mamma, sendu mér vefsíðu kvikmyndarinnar State Organs . Ég mun sýna það bekkjarfélögum mínum og vinum sem komu ekki. Ég mun deila því í hópum mínum á Facebook svo að við verðum að vernda landið okkar sem er mikilvægt að horfa á það. standa vörð um lýðræði okkar, frelsi og mannréttindi. Allir bera þessa ábyrgð.'“

Yu Guan sagði: „Skiunin og umræðurnar gengu vel. Hann sagði að vinur sinn hafi lesið rangar fréttir í erlendum fjölmiðlum í síðustu viku, en eftir að hafa horft á myndina skildi hann sannleikann og spurði hvernig ætti að læra Falun Gong.

content: الجمهور يدعم الفالون غونغ

comment_id: سمع دانيال جودوين، الذي يعمل في المجال القانوني، عن الفالون غونغ عام ٢٠١٨. وبعد مشاهدة الفيلم الوثائقي، قال إنه ينبغي توعية المزيد من الناس بجريمة الحزب الشيوعي الصيني المتمثلة في حصد الأعضاء الحية. وأضاف: "كثير من الناس لا يعرفون هذا الأمر بعد، لكن يجب أن يعرفوا هذه الفظاعة. بدأتُ أتعرف عليها عام ٢٠١٨".
قال: "الحزب الشيوعي الصيني لا يضطهد الفالون غونغ فحسب، بل يضطهد الآن أيضًا أفرادًا من جماعات أخرى. لكن الحزب الشيوعي الصيني يضطهد في الغالب ممارسي الفالون غونغ".
وباعتباره مسيحيًا، أعرب عن دعمه لحرية معتقدات ممارسي الفالون غونغ.

شاهدت الدكتورة لي، طبيبة القلب، الفيلم الوثائقي مع زوجها. قالت: "كنت أعرف أن الحزب الشيوعي الصيني يضطهد الفالون غونغ، لكنني لم أكن أعلم أن هذا الاضطهاد بهذه الشدة، حيث يُضطهد مئة مليون شخص. لم أكن أعلم أن الحزب الشيوعي الصيني يضطهد الفالون غونغ تحديدًا من قبل. الصين تعاني من مشكلة كبيرة، والحزب الشيوعي الصيني مُخطئ في هذا".

بكت باتي ويليت، المتقاعدة من شركة حاسوب في وادي السيليكون، أثناء مشاهدتها للفيلم الوثائقي. قالت: "كانت تلك أول مرة أسمع فيها عن الفالون غونغ. رؤيتي لهم وهم يتعرضون للاضطهاد أحزنتني للغاية، وذرفت الدموع في عيني. شعرتُ بما عاناه آباؤهم. لم أستطع تحمل مشاهدة بعض المشاهد".
باتي ويليت، موظفة متقاعدة في وادي السيليكون
قالت السيدة ويليت إن الفالون غونغ كان جديدًا عليها تمامًا. "أحب مبادئ الصدق والرحمة والصبر. هذا يؤثر بي. لديهم معتقدات روحية. ما حدث لهم [استئصال الأعضاء] غير مقبول بالنسبة لي.
قالت: "خصوصًا لأنهم طيبون جدًا، فمن غير المقبول تقطيع أجسادهم وهم على قيد الحياة. يبحث الأهل عن أبنائهم، لكنهم لا يجدونهم. إنه لأمرٌ مُفجع".
قال دينيس، مهندس برمجيات من أوكرانيا: "لم نسمع عن الفالون غونغ من قبل. اليوم، لم نتعرف فقط على الفالون غونغ، بل تعرفنا أيضًا على جرائم الحزب الشيوعي الصيني ضد الإنسانية".

قالت هانا، وهي أيضًا من أوكرانيا: "الحزب الشيوعي الصيني شرير، والشيوعية شريرة. وكما هو الحال مع الاتحاد السوفيتي، فالشيوعية شريرة في كل مكان. آمل أن يلعب هذا الفيلم دورًا. فكشف الحقيقة سيساعد. فكشف شر الشيوعية سيؤدي إلى تفكك الحزب الشيوعي الصيني".

لم تكن هذه هي المرة الأولى التي تسمع فيها إريكا هاثاواي، جليسة الحيوانات الأليفة، عن اضطهاد الحزب الشيوعي الصيني لفالون غونغ وجريمة استئصال الأعضاء القسري. بعد مشاهدة الفيلم الوثائقي، اكتسبت فهمًا أعمق لمدى جرائم الحزب الشيوعي الصيني. "كنت أعرف أن الحزب الشيوعي الصيني يحصد أعضاءً من الأحياء، لكنني لم أكن أعلم أن الأمر بهذا الحجم، مع احتجاز هذا العدد الكبير من الناس واستئصال أعضائهم لتحقيق الربح."
تُعجب السيدة هاثاواي بإيمان ممارسي الفالون غونغ الراسخ. "يُضطهدون حتى الموت بسبب إيمانهم، مما يُظهر ثباتهم الشديد على إيمانهم. أدعو لهم وأتمنى أن ينتهي الاضطهاد قريبًا."
قالت إن الفيلم الوثائقي ممتاز. "إنه موثوق. جميع المعلومات فيه موثوقة، وهو مُعدّ بإتقان. صُوّر بطريقة مباشرة تُشعر الناس بضرورة اتخاذ إجراء حياله."

content: رزرو یک تئاتر برای نمایش‌های بیشتر

comment_id: یکی از حضار گفت: «بسیاری از مردم نسبت به ح.ک.چ بی‌حس شده‌اند؛ آن‌ها شست‌وشو مغزی شده‌اند، غرق آسایش هستند و به بحران تایوان اهمیتی نمی‌دهند.»

آقای لی گفت که بسیاری از جوانان این فیلم را تماشا کردند، به مسئولیت خود پی بردند، به حمایت از آن برخاستند و حتی یک سالن برای نمایش‌های بیشتر رزرو کردند. مردی یک تئاتر در کائوسیونگ رزرو کرد و آقای گوان، رئیس لیون فیلم، به کائوسیونگ رفت تا پس از نمایش این فیلم، درباره آن صحبت کند.
شرارت هرگز بر خوبی غلبه نخواهد کرد

آقای لی در ادامه گفت: «تایوان دارای دموکراسی، آزادی، صلح و مهربانی است و سرزمینی مهربان و مبارک است. مردم تایوان به موجودات الهی اعتقاد دارند. کاملاً معتقدم که تایوان توسط ح.ک.چ اداره نخواهد شد، زیرا آسمان از زمان‌های قدیم بر آن نظارت داشته است.«

«اصول فالون گونگ، حقیقت، نیک‌خواهی و بردباری، نیروی قدرتمندی در جامعه است. معتقدم که قدرت خوبی قطعاً شیطان را شکست خواهد داد و شرارت هرگز بر خوبی پیروز نخواهد شد. ح.ک.چ می‌ترسد، زیرا موجودات الهی به ما کمک می‌کنند و خوبی بر شرارت پیروز می‌شود درواقع حقیقتی ابدی است.»

او به مخاطبان توصیه کرد دو کتاب را مطالعه کنند: شواهد انکارناپذیر و نه شرح و تفسیر درباره حزب کمونیست. او گفت: «نه شرح تفسیر درباره حزب کمونیست به‌طور کامل ماهیت حزب کمونیست را آشکار‌ می‌کند و ارزش خواندن دارد.»
برای حمایت و انتشار حقیقت ایستادگی کنید

دکتر چنگ چنگ‌بینگ گفت: «این نمایش فیلم بسیار موفق است. عالی است. خیلی تحت تأثیر قرار گرفتم!» او با علامت دست، آن را تأیید کرد و گفت: «ما از تمرین‌کنندگان فالون گونگ، اپک تایمز، صدای امید و سایر رسانه‌هایی که دراین‌باره گزارش می‌کنند بسیار سپاسگزاریم. همه شما فداکار و ازخودگذشته هستید، که واقعاً شگفت‌انگیز است.»
او گفت: «هریک از ما باید این روحیه را بیاموزیم، برای حمایت ایستادگی کنیم، و شجاعت افشای حقیقت و مبارزه با ح.ک.چ را داشته باشیم.»
افراد بیشتری باید از این فیلم حمایت کنند

بعد از اینکه خانم تسای هان‌لین، عضو باشگاه روتاری، این فیلم را تماشا کرد، گفت: «عمیقاً تحت تأثیر قرار گرفتم. تمرین‌کنندگان فالون گونگ را خیلی خیلی تحسین می‌کنم. در گذشته فقط می‌شنیدم که آن‌ها مورد آزار و اذیت قرار دارند، اما نمی‌دانستم چرا و نمی‌توانستم آن را درک کنم. حالا آن را به‌وضوح درک‌ می‌کنم.»

او گفت که همه باید برای تبلیغ این فیلم داوطلب شوند و همه در تایوان، باید آن را تماشا کنند: «اگرچه نمی‌توانیم این افراد تحت آزار و اذیت را نجات دهیم، اما باید داوطلبانه، حمایت کنیم و نجاتشان دهیم. این کاری است که باید انجام دهیم.»
«این فیلم واقعاً می‌تواند تایوان، تمرین‌کنندگان فالون گونگ، من، فرزندانم، خانواده‌ام و دوستانم را نجات دهد. ‌درباره آن به افراد بیشتری خواهم گفت. همه باید از این فیلم حمایت کنند.»

یکی دیگر از حضار گفت: «این بحث موفقیت‌آمیز و آموزنده بود. آنچه چندین استاد ‌درباره آن صحبت کردند به ایجاد انگیزه در دانشجویان جوان و مخاطبان برای حمایت از دموکراسی، آزادی و حقوق بشر کمک‌ می‌کند. فرزندم به من گفت: "مامان، وب‌سایت فیلم “اعضای بدن دولتی” را برایم بفرست. آن را به همکلاسی‌ها و دوستانم که نیامده‌اند نشان خواهم داد. آن را در گروه‌هایم در فیس‌بوک به اشتراک خواهم گذاشت تا افراد بیشتری بتوانند آن را تماشا کنند. این خیلی مهم است. ما باید برای حفاظت از کشورمان و حفظ دموکراسی، آزادی و حقوق بشر خود پیش‌قدم شویم. این مسئولیت همه است.»

یو گوان اظهار کرد: «این نمایش و بحث به‌خوبی پیش رفت.» او گفت که دوستش هفته گذشته گزارش‌های نادرست را در رسانه‌های خارج از کشور خواند، اما پس از تماشای این فیلم، حقیقت را فهمید و پرسید که چگونه فالون گونگ را یاد بگیرد.
